---
import Layout from '../components/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | AuralNet">
  
  <div class="min-h-screen pt-32 px-8 md:px-16 pb-32 max-w-[1400px] mx-auto">
    
    <!-- Header: The Lost Archive -->
    <header class="mb-32">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-start border-b border-foreground/20 pb-8 mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">[ ABOUT / 002 ]</h1>
        <div class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground text-right hidden md:block">
          Owly Labs Intelligence<br/>
          Est. 2025
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-5xl md:text-8xl font-bold tracking-tighter mb-12 max-w-4xl leading-[0.9]">
        The Lost<br/>
        Archive.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          Every two weeks, a language dies. With it goes centuries of knowledge, unique perspectives on reality, and the intimate connection between generations.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed opacity-80">
          Owly Labs exists to reverse this trend. We are not a tech company. We are a digital preservation institute building the infrastructure to decode, archive, and revitalize the world's linguistic heritage through advanced AI.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- The Constitution -->
    <section>
      <div class="border-t border-foreground/20 pt-8 mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest mb-4 text-primary">Charter</h3>
        <h4 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold mb-12">The Protocol</h4>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-px bg-foreground/10 border border-foreground/10">
        
        <div class="bg-background p-12 hover:bg-foreground/5 transition-colors">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs mb-4 opacity-50">ARTICLE I</div>
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Fair Trade Data</h3>
          <p class="opacity-70 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
            We do not extract data; we partner with communities. Contributors retain sovereignty over their cultural assets. 
            Value generated from the AuralNet registry is reinvested into language revitalization programs.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-background p-12 hover:bg-foreground/5 transition-colors">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs mb-4 opacity-50">ARTICLE II</div>
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">No Cloning</h3>
          <p class="opacity-70 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
            Our models learn *how* people speak, not *who* is speaking. We explicitly prohibit the generation of individual voice clones. 
            Our technology is designed for understanding (ASR/NLU), not impersonation (TTS).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-background p-12 hover:bg-foreground/5 transition-colors">
          <div class="font-mono text-xs mb-4 opacity-50">ARTICLE III</div>
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Radical Inclusion</h3>
          <p class="opacity-70 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
            "Standard" languages are a myth. Real human communication is messy, dialect-rich, and context-dependent. 
            We build for the reality of the street, not the classroom.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>
